(135, 255, 'Peggy Teich', 'peggy-teich', '<h6>Vice President</h6>\r\n<a href="mailto:peggy@writopialab.org" class="link-email"><i class="icon-envelope"></i>peggy@writopialab.org</a>\r\n<p>Peggy Teich is a business librarian, an educator, and a Writopia mom. She has been advising the Writopia team on research methods and community building since the fall of 2009. An adjunct librarian at CUNYs Baruch College for over twelve years, she was previously Vice President and manager of Citibanks Research library. She worked as a business librarian at an investment bank and advertising agency as well. In addition to her corporate experience, Peggy taught business librarianship in the Masters of library science programs at Pratt Institute, Columbia University and Rutgers. She has been a guest speaker and lecturer at numerous professional association meetings, and graduate schools locally and lectured on business librarianship at the cole des Sciences de lInformation, part of the Ministry of Economic Planning in Rabat Morocco. She has contributed to numerous professional publications and most recently served as a chapter consultant on The Basic Business Librarian  Core Resources, Greenwood Press 2002.</p>', '', -2, 88, '2013-06-02 02:18:21', 42, '', '2013-06-02 02:22:04', 42, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-06-02 02:18:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"images\\/140x105.gif","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":null,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":null,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":null,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"",