(1435, 'ARI_IMAGE_SLIDER_MODULE', 'ARI Image Slider module based on <a href=\'http://nivo.dev7studios.com/\' target=\'_blank\' title=\'Nivo Slider\'>Nivo Slider</a> jQuery plugin and provides possibility to create awesome image slider based on images from specific folder(s). Main features:<ul><li>16 transition effects;</li><li>No flash. Pure javascript and CSS;</li><li>Can sort images by file name, modified date or in random order;</li><li>Supports keyboard navigation;</li><li>Provide ability to create your own themes;</li><li>Can start slideshow automatically;</li><li>Supports possibility to show images titles and define redirect links which you can define in INI file;</li><li>Can be integrated with different lightbox extensions;</li><li>Works in all modern browsers.</li></ul><br /><br /><b>How to use?</b><br /><br />Configure main module parameters, specify relative path to images in \'Image path\' parameter. Place each  path to image folder on new line in \'Image path\' textarea. Joomla! root directory will be used as root path for this folders. It means that if you want to show images from [joomla_dir]/images/slides folder, type in \'Image path\' parameter the following value images/slides.  Set \'Scan subfolders\' parameter to \'Yes\', if you want to include images from subfolders to image slideshow.<br/><br/>You can also define titles and redirect links for images. For this place INI file with name from \'Description file\' parameter in necessary folder with images. Sample INI file you can download <a href=\'../modules/mod_ariimageslider/ariimageslider.ini\' target=\'_blank\'>here</a>. In [DESCRIPTION] section place image file name and title for image in the following format: [file_name]=[title]. Where [file_name] is image file name and [title] is image title. In [LINK] section place image file name and link for image in the following format: [file_name]=[link]. Where [file_name] is image file name and [link] is image title. If you use non-english characters in INI file, save this file in UTF-8 encoding.<br/><br/> If you want to have different INI files and load one of them based on active site langauge, enable \'Support multi-language description\' option and create INI files with file name in the following format: [base_ini_filename].[lang_tag].ini where [base_ini_filename] is base file name without extension which indicated in \'Description file\' parameter, [lang_tag] is tag of active site language. For example, if active language is \'Russian\' and value of \'\'Description file\' parameter is \'ariimageslider.ini\' create file with name ariimageslider.ru-RU.ini<br /><br /><br /><b>How to integrate it with lightbox?</b><br /><br />The module can display large images in a lightbox. The module supports the following lightbox extensions:<ul><li><a href=\'http://www.ari-soft.com/Joomla-Components/ARI-Sexy-Lightbox/Detailed-product-flyer.html\' title=\'ARI Sexy Lightbox\' target=\'_blank\'>ARI Sexy Lightbox</a>. Install \'System - ARI Sexy Lightbox\' plugin;</li><li><a href=\'http://www.ari-soft.com/Joomla-Components/ARI-Fancybox/Detailed-product-flyer.html\' title=\'ARI Fancybox\' target=\'_blank\'>ARI Fancybox</a>. Install \'System - ARI Fancybox\' plugin;</li><li><a href=\'http://www.ari-soft.com/Joomla-Components/ARI-Colorbox/Detailed-product-flyer.html\' title=\'ARI Colorbox\' target=\'_blank\'>ARI Colorbox</a>. Install \'System - ARI Colorbox\' plugin;</li><li><a href=\'http://www.ari-soft.com/Joomla-Components/ARI-Pretty-Photo/Detailed-product-flyer.html\' title=\'ARI Pretty Photo\' target=\'_blank\'>ARI Pretty Photo</a>. Install \'System - ARI Pretty Photo\' plugin;</li><li><a href=\'http://ninjaforge.com/joomla15/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=88&Itemid=105\' title=\'Ninja Shadowbox\' target=\'_blank\'>Ninja Shadowbox</a>. Install \'System - Ninja Shadowbox\' plugin;</li><li>Core Joomla! lightbox. Core Joomla! SqueezeBox MooTools lightbox plugin will be used.</li></ul><br /><br /><b>How to create new theme?</b><br /><br />You can use \'default\' theme as start point for creating your own theme. \'default\' theme is located by the following path \'[joomla_dir]/modules/mod_ariimageslider/mod_ariimageslider/js/themes/default\'. You can download this folder to your computer, modify style.css file for your needs, rename \'default\' folder to new theme name, for example \'my_own_theme\' and upload this folder to \'[joomla_dir]/modules/mod_ariimageslider/mod_ariimageslider/js/themes\' directory on your server. Now you can choose new theme in \'Theme\' dropdown on module settings page.<br /><br /><br />If you use <b>ARI Image Slider</b> extension, please post a rating and a review at the <a href=\'http://extensions.joomla.org/extensions/photos-a-images/images-slideshow/13262\' target=\'_blank\' title=\'ARI Image Slider on JED\'>Joomla! Extensions Directory</a>.<br /><br />If you have any questions you feel free to ask them on our <a href=\'http://www.ari-soft.com/ARI-Image-Slider/\' target=\'_blank\'>forum</a> or by <a href=\'mailto:info@ari-soft.com\'>email</a>.', '/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/github/writopialab/language/en-GB/en-GB.mod_ariimageslider.ini'),
